539
01:38:38 --> 01:38:48
You were a glorified accountant.

540
01:38:49 --> 01:38:59
What could you possibly have
on all of them that we could charge?

541
01:39:00 --> 01:39:10
I'm good with calculation.
I handled all their investments.

542
01:39:11 --> 01:39:21
One big pot.

543
01:39:22 --> 01:39:32
Got it.

544
01:39:33 --> 01:39:43
One minute.

545
01:39:44 --> 01:39:54
RICO. If they pooled their money...

546
01:39:55 --> 01:40:05
...we can charge them
as one criminal conspiracy.

547
01:40:06 --> 01:40:16
Charge them with what?

548
01:40:17 --> 01:40:27
In a RICO case, if you can charge
one of them with a felony...

549
01:40:28 --> 01:40:38
You can charge all of them with it.
That's great.

550
01:40:39 --> 01:40:49
Mr. Lau.

551
01:40:50 --> 01:41:00
What kind of details do you have
about this communal fund?

552
01:41:01 --> 01:41:11
- Ledgers...?
- Immunity, protection...

553
01:41:12 --> 01:41:22
...a chartered plane back to Hong Kong.
- After you testify in open court.

554
01:41:23 --> 01:41:33
I'm just curious.
With all your clients locked up...

555
01:41:34 --> 01:41:44
...what's gonna happen
with all that money?

556
01:41:45 --> 01:41:55
Like I said, I'm good with calculation.

557
01:41:56 --> 01:42:06
He can't go to County.
I'll keep him here in the holding cells.

558
01:42:07 --> 01:42:17
What is this, Gordon, your fortress?

559
01:42:18 --> 01:42:28
Well, you trust them over at County?

560
01:42:29 --> 01:42:39
I don't trust them here.

561
01:42:40 --> 01:42:50
Lau stays.

562
01:42:51 --> 01:43:01
<i>Well, I don 't know about</i>
<i>Mr. Lau's travel arrangements...</i>

563
01:43:02 --> 01:43:12
<i>... but I'm sure glad he's back.</i>

564
01:43:13 --> 01:43:23
Put word out. We hire the clown.

565
01:43:24 --> 01:43:34
He was right.
We have to fix real problem.

566
01:43:35 --> 01:43:45
Batman.

567
01:43:46 --> 01:43:56
<i>- I'm not aware of any participation...</i>
- Our boy looks good on the tube.

568
01:43:57 --> 01:44:07
You sure you wanna embarrass me
in front of my friends?

569
01:44:08 --> 01:44:18
Oh, don't worry. They're coming too.

570
01:44:19 --> 01:44:29
STEPHENS:
Have a nice trip. See you next fall.

571
01:44:30 --> 01:44:40
WOMAN: <i>Seven hundred</i>
<i>twelve counts of extortion.</i>

572
01:44:41 --> 01:44:51
<i>Eight hundred and forty-nine</i>
<i>counts of racketeering.</i>

573
01:44:52 --> 01:45:02
Two hundred and forty-six
counts of fraud.

574
01:45:03 --> 01:45:13
Eighty-seven counts
of conspiracy murder.

575
01:45:14 --> 01:45:24
Five hundred and twenty-seven
counts of obstruction of justice.

576
01:45:25 --> 01:45:35
How do the defendants plead?

577
01:45:36 --> 01:45:46
[CLAMORING]

578
01:45:47 --> 01:45:57
Order in the court.

579
01:45:58 --> 01:46:08
MAYOR: <i>Five hundred and forty-nine</i>
<i>criminals at once.</i>

580
01:46:09 --> 01:46:19
How did you convince Surrillo
to hear this farce?

581
01:46:20 --> 01:46:30
She shares my enthusiasm for justice.
After all, she is a judge.

582
01:46:31 --> 01:46:41
Even if you blow enough smoke
to get convictions out of Surrillo...

583
01:46:42 --> 01:46:52
...you're gonna set
a new record at appeals.

584
01:46:53 --> 01:47:03
It won't matter.
The head guys make bail, sure.

585
01:47:04 --> 01:47:14
But the midlevel guys, they can't.

586
01:47:15 --> 01:47:25
They can't afford to be off the streets.

587
01:47:26 --> 01:47:36
They'll cut deals that
include some jail time.

588
01:47:37 --> 01:47:47
Think of all you could do
with 18 months of clean streets.

589
01:47:48 --> 01:47:58
LOEB: Mr. Mayor, you can't...
- No, get out. Both of you.

590
01:47:59 --> 01:48:09
Sit down.

591
01:48:10 --> 01:48:20
The public likes you. That's the
only reason that this might fly.

592
01:48:21 --> 01:48:31
But that means it's on you.

593
01:48:32 --> 01:48:42
They're all gonna come after you now,
and not just the Mob.

594
01:48:43 --> 01:48:53
Politicians, journalists, cops.

595
01:48:54 --> 01:49:04
Anyone whose wallet's
about to get lighter.

596
01:49:05 --> 01:49:15
Are you up to it? You'd better be.

597
01:49:16 --> 01:49:26
Because they get anything on you...

598
01:49:27 --> 01:49:37
...and those criminals are back on the
streets, followed swiftly by you and me.

599
01:49:38 --> 01:49:48
Jesus!

600
01:49:49 --> 01:49:59
[SIRENS WAILING]

601
01:50:00 --> 01:50:10
ALFRED: I think your fundraiser
will be a great success, sir.

602
01:50:11 --> 01:50:21
BRUCE: And why do you think I wanna
hold a party for Harvey Dent?

603
01:50:22 --> 01:50:32
I assumed it was your usual reason
for socializing beyond myself...

604
01:50:33 --> 01:50:43
...and the scum of Gotham's underbelly:

605
01:50:44 --> 01:50:54
To try to impress Miss Dawes.

606
01:50:55 --> 01:51:05
Very droll, but very wrong.
Actually, it's Dent.

607
01:51:06 --> 01:51:16
ENGEL [ON TV]: <i>Police released video</i>
<i>footage found concealed on the body.</i>

608
01:51:17 --> 01:51:27
<i>Sensitive viewers, be aware.</i>
<i>The image is disturbing.</i>

609
01:51:28 --> 01:51:38
JOKER:
<i>Tell them your name.</i>

610
01:51:39 --> 01:51:49
<i>Brian Douglas.</i>

611
01:51:50 --> 01:52:00
[JOKER LAUGHS]

612
01:52:01 --> 01:52:11
JOKER:
<i>And are you the real Batman?</i>

613
01:52:12 --> 01:52:22
BRIAN: <i>No.</i>
JOKER: <i>No?</i>

614
01:52:23 --> 01:52:33
<i>- No.</i>
<i>- No?</i>

615
01:52:34 --> 01:52:44
<i>Then why do you dress up like him?</i>

616
01:52:45 --> 01:52:55
[JOKER LAUGHS]

617
01:52:56 --> 01:53:06
<i>Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!</i>

618
01:53:07 --> 01:53:17
BRIAN: <i>Because he's a symbol that we</i>
<i>don 't have to be afraid of scum like you.</i>

619
01:53:18 --> 01:53:28
<i>Yeah. You do, Brian. You really do.</i>

620
01:53:29 --> 01:53:39
<i>Huh? Yeah. Oh, shh, shh, shh.</i>

621
01:53:40 --> 01:53:50
<i>So you think Batman 's</i>
<i>made Gotham a better place? Hm?</i>

622
01:53:51 --> 01:54:01
<i>Look at me.</i>

623
01:54:02 --> 01:54:12
<i>Look at me!</i>

624
01:54:13 --> 01:54:23
<i>You see, this is how crazy</i>
<i>Batman 's made Gotham.</i>

625
01:54:24 --> 01:54:34
<i>You want order in Gotham...</i>

626
01:54:35 --> 01:54:45
<i>... Batman must take off his mask</i>
<i>and turn himself in.</i>

627
01:54:46 --> 01:54:56
<i>Oh, and every day he doesn 't,</i>
<i>people will die.</i>

628
01:54:57 --> 01:55:07
<i>Starting tonight.</i>

629
01:55:08 --> 01:55:18
<i>I'm a man of my word.</i>

630
01:55:19 --> 01:55:29
[LAUGHING]

631
01:55:30 --> 01:55:40
[BRIAN SCREAMING]

632
01:55:41 --> 01:55:51
[CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING]

633
01:55:52 --> 01:56:02
Harvey Dent,
scourge of the underworld...

634
01:56:03 --> 01:56:13
...scared stiff by the trust-fund brigade.

635
01:56:14 --> 01:56:24
- I'll be back.
- Rachel.

636
01:56:25 --> 01:56:35
A little liquid courage, Mr. Dent?

637
01:56:36 --> 01:56:46
- Thank you. Alfred, right?
- That's right, sir.

638
01:56:47 --> 01:56:57
Rachel talks about you all the time.
You've known her her whole life.

639
01:56:58 --> 01:57:08
Not yet, sir.

640
01:57:09 --> 01:57:19
Any psychotic ex-boyfriends
I should be aware of?

641
01:57:20 --> 01:57:30
Oh, you have no idea.

642
01:57:31 --> 01:57:41
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

643
01:57:42 --> 01:57:52
BRUCE: I'm sorry that I'm late.

644
01:57:53 --> 01:58:03
I'm glad to see
that you all got started without me.

645
01:58:04 --> 01:58:14
Now, where is Harvey? Where...?

646
01:58:15 --> 01:58:25
Harvey Dent, the man of the hour.

647
01:58:26 --> 01:58:36
Where's Rachel Dawes?

648
01:58:37 --> 01:58:47
She is my oldest friend. Come here.

649
01:58:48 --> 01:58:58
When Rachel first told me she
was dating Harvey Dent...

650
01:58:59 --> 01:59:09
...I had one thing to say:

651
01:59:10 --> 01:59:20
"The guy from those God-awful
campaign commercials?"

652
01:59:21 --> 01:59:31
"I believe in Harvey Dent."
Yeah, nice slogan, Harvey.

653
01:59:32 --> 01:59:42
But it caught Rachel's attention.

654
01:59:43 --> 01:59:53
And then I started to pay attention
to Harvey...

655
01:59:54 --> 02:00:04
...and all that he's been doing
as our new DA.

656
02:00:05 --> 02:00:15
And you know what?

657
02:00:16 --> 02:00:26
I believe in Harvey Dent.

658
02:00:27 --> 02:00:37
I believe that on his watch,
Gotham can feel...

659
02:00:38 --> 02:00:48
...a little safer, a little more optimistic.

660
02:00:49 --> 02:00:59
Look at this face. This is the face
of Gotham's bright future.

661
02:01:00 --> 02:01:10
To Harvey Dent. Let's hear it for him.

662
02:01:11 --> 02:01:21
MAN:
Harvey.

663
02:01:22 --> 02:01:32
Harvey may not know you
well enough...

664
02:01:33 --> 02:01:43
...to understand you're
making fun of him...

665
02:01:44 --> 02:01:54
...but I do.
- No, I meant every word.

666
02:01:55 --> 02:02:05
You know that day
that you once told me about...

667
02:02:06 --> 02:02:16
...when Gotham would no longer
need Batman?

668
02:02:17 --> 02:02:27
- It's coming.
- Bruce.

669
02:02:28 --> 02:02:38
- You can't ask me to wait for that.
- It's happening now. Harvey is that hero.

670
02:02:39 --> 02:02:49
He locked up half of the city's criminals,
and he did it without wearing a mask.

671
02:02:50 --> 02:03:00
Gotham needs a hero with a face.

672
02:03:01 --> 02:03:11
DENT: You can throw a party, Wayne,
I'll give you that.

673
02:03:12 --> 02:03:22
Thanks again.

674
02:03:23 --> 02:03:33
You mind if I borrow Rachel?

675
02:03:34 --> 02:03:44
Lieutenant, that joker card
pinned to the body?

676
02:03:45 --> 02:03:55
Forensics found three sets of DNA.

677
02:03:56 --> 02:04:06
- Any matches?
- All three.

678
02:04:07 --> 02:04:17
The DNA belongs to Judge Surrillo,
Harvey Dent and Commissioner Loeb.

679
02:04:18 --> 02:04:28
The Joker's telling us
who he's targeting.

680
02:04:29 --> 02:04:39
Get a unit over to Surrillo's house.
Tell Wuertz to find Dent.

681
02:04:40 --> 02:04:50
Protective custody.
Where's the commissioner?

682
02:04:51 --> 02:05:01
- City hall.
- Seal the building.

683
02:05:02 --> 02:05:12
- No one in or out till I get there.
- Got it.

684
02:05:13 --> 02:05:23
Gordon. What are you up to?

685
02:05:24 --> 02:05:34
We're secure. I want a floor-by-floor
search of the entire building.

686
02:05:35 --> 02:05:45
We believe the Joker's
made a threat against your life.

687
02:05:46 --> 02:05:56
These are dangerous people.

688
02:05:57 --> 02:06:07
You're not giving me
a lot of information.

689
02:06:08 --> 02:06:18
Even we don't know
where you're going.

690
02:06:19 --> 02:06:29
Take the envelope, get in, open it.
It'll tell you where you're headed.

691
02:06:30 --> 02:06:40
You can't leave me alone
with these people.

692
02:06:41 --> 02:06:51
The whole Mob's after you
and you're worried about these guys?

693
02:06:52 --> 02:07:02
Compared to this,
the Mob doesn't scare me.

694
02:07:03 --> 02:07:13
Gordon, you're unlikely to discover this
for yourself, so...

695
02:07:14 --> 02:07:24
...take my word, the police commissioner
earns a lot of threats.

696
02:07:25 --> 02:07:35
I found the appropriate response
to these situations a long time ago.

697
02:07:36 --> 02:07:46
Them gunning for you
makes you see things clearly.

698
02:07:47 --> 02:07:57
Yeah, I bet.

699
02:07:58 --> 02:08:08
Yeah. It makes you think about things
you couldn't stand losing...

700
02:08:09 --> 02:08:19
...about who you wanna
spend your life with.

701
02:08:20 --> 02:08:30
- That's a pretty big commitment.
- Not if the Mob has their way.

702
02:08:31 --> 02:08:41
You get to explain to my wife...

703
02:08:42 --> 02:08:52
...why I'm late for dinner.

704
02:08:53 --> 02:09:03
Sir, the joker card
had traces of your DNA on it.

705
02:09:04 --> 02:09:14
- Don't do that.
- All right.

706
02:09:15 --> 02:09:25
- Let's be serious, then.
- Okay.

707
02:09:26 --> 02:09:36
What's your answer?

708
02:09:37 --> 02:09:47
I don't have an answer.

709
02:09:48 --> 02:09:58
How'd they get my DNA?

710
02:09:59 --> 02:10:09
Somebody with access
to your office or house...

711
02:10:10 --> 02:10:20
...must have lifted a tissue
or a glass... Wait! Wait!

712
02:10:21 --> 02:10:31
- Well, I guess no answer is a no.
- Harvey.

713
02:10:32 --> 02:10:42
- It's someone else, isn't it?
- Harvey.

714
02:10:43 --> 02:10:53
Just tell me it's not Wayne.
The guy's a complete f...

715
02:10:54 --> 02:11:04
What are you doing?

716
02:11:05 --> 02:11:15
GORDON:
Oh, shit.

717
02:11:16 --> 02:11:26
[LOEB COUGHING]

718
02:11:27 --> 02:11:37
GORDON:
Get a medic!

719
02:11:38 --> 02:11:48
They've come for him.

720
02:11:49 --> 02:11:59
We made it.

721
02:12:00 --> 02:12:10
Stay hidden.

722
02:12:11 --> 02:12:21
[SHOTGUN BLAST]

723
02:12:22 --> 02:12:32
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.

724
02:12:33 --> 02:12:43
We are tonight's entertainment.

725
02:12:44 --> 02:12:54
I only have one question:

726
02:12:55 --> 02:13:05
Where is Harvey Dent?

727
02:13:06 --> 02:13:16
You know where Harvey is?
You know who he is?

728
02:13:17 --> 02:13:27
THUG:
Hands up, pretty boy.

729
02:13:28 --> 02:13:38
[THUG GRUNTING]

730
02:13:39 --> 02:13:49
Do you know where I can find Harvey?
I need to talk to him.

731
02:13:50 --> 02:14:00
Just something little, huh? No.

732
02:14:01 --> 02:14:11
What's going on out there? Wayne!

733
02:14:12 --> 02:14:22
Oh, thank God, you've
got a panic room.

734
02:14:23 --> 02:14:33
MAN: Hey, wait...

735
02:14:34 --> 02:14:44
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

736
02:14:45 --> 02:14:55
You know, I'll settle for his loved ones.

737
02:14:56 --> 02:15:06
We're not intimidated by thugs.

738
02:15:07 --> 02:15:17
You know...

739
02:15:18 --> 02:15:28
...you remind me of my father.

740
02:15:29 --> 02:15:39
I hated my father.

741
02:15:40 --> 02:15:50
RACHEL:
Okay, stop.

742
02:15:51 --> 02:16:01
Well, hello, beautiful.

743
02:16:02 --> 02:16:12
You must be Harvey's squeeze. Hm?

744
02:16:13 --> 02:16:23
And you are beautiful.

745
02:16:24 --> 02:16:34
You look nervous. Is it the scars?

746
02:16:35 --> 02:16:45
You wanna know how I got them?

747
02:16:46 --> 02:16:56
Come here. Hey.

748
02:16:57 --> 02:17:07
Look at me.

749
02:17:08 --> 02:17:18
So I had a wife.
She was beautiful, like you...

750
02:17:19 --> 02:17:29
...who tells me I worry too much...

751
02:17:30 --> 02:17:40
...who tells me I ought to smile more...

752
02:17:41 --> 02:17:51
...who gambles and gets in deep
with the sharks. Hey.

753
02:17:52 --> 02:18:02
One day they carve her face.

754
02:18:03 --> 02:18:13
And we have no money for surgeries.
She can't take it.

755
02:18:14 --> 02:18:24
I just wanna see her smile again. Hm?

756
02:18:25 --> 02:18:35
I just want her to know
that I don't care about the scars.

757
02:18:36 --> 02:18:46
So...

758
02:18:47 --> 02:18:57
...I stick a razor in my mouth
and do this...

759
02:18:58 --> 02:19:08
...to myself.

760
02:19:09 --> 02:19:19
And you know what?
She can't stand the sight of me.

761
02:19:20 --> 02:19:30
She leaves.

762
02:19:31 --> 02:19:41
Now I see the funny side.

763
02:19:42 --> 02:19:52
Now I'm always smiling.

764
02:19:53 --> 02:20:03
[LAUGHS]

765
02:20:04 --> 02:20:14
You got a little fight in you. I like that.

766
02:20:15 --> 02:20:25
BATMAN:
Then you're gonna love me.

767
02:20:26 --> 02:20:36
[GRUNTING]

768
02:20:37 --> 02:20:47
[BATMAN YELLS]

769
02:20:48 --> 02:20:58
Drop the gun.

770
02:20:59 --> 02:21:09
Oh, sure. You just take off
your little mask...

771
02:21:10 --> 02:21:20
...and show us all who
you really are. Hm?

772
02:21:21 --> 02:21:31
Let her go.

773
02:21:32 --> 02:21:42
Very poor choice of words.

774
02:21:43 --> 02:21:53
[LAUGHS]

775
02:21:54 --> 02:22:04
[RACHEL SCREAMING]

776
02:22:05 --> 02:22:15
Are you all right?

777
02:22:16 --> 02:22:26
Let's not do that again.

778
02:22:27 --> 02:22:37
- Is Harvey okay?
- He's safe.

779
02:22:38 --> 02:22:48
Thank you.

780
02:22:49 --> 02:22:59
Jim, it's over.

781
02:23:00 --> 02:23:10
As long as they don't get to Lau,
we've cut off their funds.

782
02:23:11 --> 02:23:21
The prosecution's over.

783
02:23:22 --> 02:23:32
Nobody's standing up
in front of a judge...

784
02:23:33 --> 02:23:43
...while judges and police commissioners
are getting blown away.

785
02:23:44 --> 02:23:54
- What about Dent?
- He's got any sense...

786
02:23:55 --> 02:24:05
...Dent's halfway to Mex...

787
02:24:06 --> 02:24:16
DENT:
So where do you keep your trash?

788
02:24:17 --> 02:24:27
You're due in court. I need you alive
long enough to get you on the record.

789
02:24:28 --> 02:24:38
You can't protect me.
You can't even protect yourselves.

790
02:24:39 --> 02:24:49
You refuse to cooperate, you're not
coming back here, you go to County.

791
02:24:50 --> 02:25:00
How long do you calculate
you'll last in there?

792
02:25:01 --> 02:25:11
Targeting me won't get their money.

793
02:25:12 --> 02:25:22
I knew the Mob wouldn't go
down easily...

794
02:25:23 --> 02:25:33
...but this is different.
They crossed a line.

795
02:25:34 --> 02:25:44
You crossed the line first.

796
02:25:45 --> 02:25:55
You squeezed them, you hammered them
to the point of desperation.

797
02:25:56 --> 02:26:06
And in their desperation, they turned to
a man they didn't fully understand.

798
02:26:07 --> 02:26:17
Criminals aren't complicated, Alfred.

799
02:26:18 --> 02:26:28
We just need to figure out
what he's after.

800
02:26:29 --> 02:26:39
ALFRED:
With respect, Master Wayne...

801
02:26:40 --> 02:26:50
...perhaps this is a man
you don't fully understand either.

802
02:26:51 --> 02:27:01
A long time ago, I was in Burma...

803
02:27:02 --> 02:27:12
...and my friends and I were working
for the local government.

804
02:27:13 --> 02:27:23
They were trying to buy
the loyalty of tribal leaders...

805
02:27:24 --> 02:27:34
...by bribing them with
precious stones...

806
02:27:35 --> 02:27:45
...but their caravans were being raided
in a forest north of Rangoon by a bandit.

807
02:27:46 --> 02:27:56
So we went looking for the stones.

808
02:27:57 --> 02:28:07
But in six months, we never
met anyone who traded with him.

809
02:28:08 --> 02:28:18
One day, I saw a child
playing with a ruby...

810
02:28:19 --> 02:28:29
...the size of a tangerine.

811
02:28:30 --> 02:28:40
The bandit had been
throwing them away.

812
02:28:41 --> 02:28:51
- So why steal them?
- Because he thought it was good sport.

813
02:28:52 --> 02:29:02
Because some men aren't looking
for anything logical, like money.

814
02:29:03 --> 02:29:13
They can't be bought, bullied,
reasoned or negotiated with.

815
02:29:14 --> 02:29:24
Some men just wanna
watch the world burn.

816
02:29:25 --> 02:29:35
[VOICES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

817
02:29:36 --> 02:29:46
WOMAN:
<i>Your name, sir?</i>

818
02:29:47 --> 02:29:57
JOKER: <i>Eighth and Orchard.</i>
<i>You'll find Harvey Dent there.</i>

819
02:29:58 --> 02:30:08
BATMAN:
Check the names.

820
02:30:09 --> 02:30:19
"Richard Dent."

821
02:30:20 --> 02:30:30
"Patrick Harvey."

822
02:30:31 --> 02:30:41
Harvey Dent.

823
02:30:42 --> 02:30:52
I need 10 minutes with the scene
before your men contaminate it.

824
02:30:53 --> 02:31:03
It's because of you
these guys are dead...

825
02:31:04 --> 02:31:14
Detective!

826
02:31:15 --> 02:31:25
Give us a minute, guys.

827
02:31:26 --> 02:31:36
That's brick underneath.

828
02:31:37 --> 02:31:47
Gonna take ballistics
off a shattered bullet?

829
02:31:48 --> 02:31:58
No.

830
02:31:59 --> 02:32:09
Fingerprints.

831
02:32:10 --> 02:32:20
Whatever you're gonna do, do it fast.

832
02:32:21 --> 02:32:31
Because we found his next target.
He's put it in tomorrow's paper.

833
02:32:32 --> 02:32:42
I'm not sure
you made it loud enough, sir.

834
02:32:43 --> 02:32:53
What can I do for you, Mr. Reese?

835
02:32:54 --> 02:33:04
You wanted me to do the diligence
on the LSI Holdings deal again.

836
02:33:05 --> 02:33:15
Well, I found some irregularities.

837
02:33:16 --> 02:33:26
Their CEO is in police custody.

838
02:33:27 --> 02:33:37
No, not with their numbers, with yours.

839
02:33:38 --> 02:33:48
Applied Sciences. Whole division
of Wayne Enterprises...

840
02:33:49 --> 02:33:59
...just disappeared overnight.

841
02:34:00 --> 02:34:10
I went down to the archives
and I started pulling some old files.

842
02:34:11 --> 02:34:21
Don't tell me you didn't
recognize your baby...

843
02:34:22 --> 02:34:32
...pancaking cop cars
on the evening news.

844
02:34:33 --> 02:34:43
Now you got the entire R & D
Department burning through cash...

845
02:34:44 --> 02:34:54
...claiming it's related to
cell phones for the Army?

846
02:34:55 --> 02:35:05
What are you building for him now,
a rocket ship?

847
02:35:06 --> 02:35:16
I want...

848
02:35:17 --> 02:35:27
...$ 10 million a year
for the rest of my life.

849
02:35:28 --> 02:35:38
Let me get this straight.

850
02:35:39 --> 02:35:49
You think that your client...

851
02:35:50 --> 02:36:00
One of the wealthiest,
most powerful men in the world...

852
02:36:01 --> 02:36:11
...is secretly a vigilante...

853
02:36:12 --> 02:36:22
...who spends his nights beating
criminals to a pulp with his bare hands...

854
02:36:23 --> 02:36:33
...and your plan
is to blackmail this person?

855
02:36:34 --> 02:36:44
Good luck.

856
02:36:45 --> 02:36:55
When...

857
02:36:56 --> 02:37:06
Keep that.

858
02:37:07 --> 02:37:17
FOX:
This is your original scan.

859
02:37:18 --> 02:37:28
Here it is reengineered.

860
02:37:29 --> 02:37:39
And there's the thumbprint he left
when he pushed the round in the clip.

861
02:37:40 --> 02:37:50
I'll get you a copy.

862
02:37:51 --> 02:38:01
Mr. Wayne, did you reassign R & D?

863
02:38:02 --> 02:38:12
Yeah. Government
telecommunications project.

864
02:38:13 --> 02:38:23
Wasn't aware
we had any government contracts.

865
02:38:24 --> 02:38:34
You know, Lucius, I'm playing this one
pretty close to the chest.

866
02:38:35 --> 02:38:45
Fair enough.

867
02:38:46 --> 02:38:56
ENGEL: With no word
from the Batman...

868
02:38:57 --> 02:39:07
...even as they mourn
Commissioner Loeb...

869
02:39:08 --> 02:39:18
...these cops have to wonder if
the Joker will make good on his threat...

870
02:39:19 --> 02:39:29
...in the obituary column of
<i>The Gotham Times</i> to kill the mayor.

871
02:39:30 --> 02:39:40
I've checked all the databases.
There are four possibles.

872
02:39:41 --> 02:39:51
Cross-reference the addresses.

873
02:39:52 --> 02:40:02
Look for Parkside,
overlooking the parade.

874
02:40:03 --> 02:40:13
I got one.

875
02:40:14 --> 02:40:24
Melvin White,
1502 Randolph Apartments.

876
02:40:25 --> 02:40:35
Aggravated assault,
moved to Arkham twice.

877
02:40:36 --> 02:40:46
What do you got on the roof?

878
02:40:47 --> 02:40:57
We're tight, but frankly,
there's a lot of windows up here.

879
02:40:58 --> 02:41:08
Commissioner Loeb dedicated his life
to law enforcement...

880
02:41:09 --> 02:41:19
...and to the protection
of his community.

881
02:41:20 --> 02:41:30
I remember when I first took office...

882
02:41:31 --> 02:41:41
...and I asked if he wanted
to stay on as commissioner.

883
02:41:42 --> 02:41:52
And he said he would, provided
I kept my politics out of his office.

884
02:41:53 --> 02:42:03
Clearly he was not a man who minced
words, nor should he have been.

885
02:42:04 --> 02:42:14
A number of policies that he enacted
as commissioner were unpopular.

886
02:42:15 --> 02:42:25
Policies that flooded my office
with angry calls and letters...

887
02:42:26 --> 02:42:36
- Who's that?
- What happened?

888
02:42:37 --> 02:42:47
They took our guns.

889
02:42:48 --> 02:42:58
And our uniforms.

890
02:42:59 --> 02:43:09
[TICKING]

891
02:43:10 --> 02:43:20
MAYOR: And as we recognize
the sacrifice of this man...

892
02:43:21 --> 02:43:31
...we must remember that vigilance
is the price of safety.

893
02:43:32 --> 02:43:42
Stand by. Honor guard.

894
02:43:43 --> 02:43:53
Attention. Port arms.

895
02:43:54 --> 02:44:04
Ready! Aim! Fire!

896
02:44:05 --> 02:44:15
Ready! Aim!

897
02:44:16 --> 02:44:26
[TIMER DINGS]

898
02:44:27 --> 02:44:37
Ready! Aim!

899
02:44:38 --> 02:44:48
[CROWD SCREAMING]

900
02:44:49 --> 02:44:59
[GUNSHOTS]

901
02:45:00 --> 02:45:10
OFFICER:
Stay down! Don't move!

902
02:45:11 --> 02:45:21
STEPHENS:
Mr. Mayor. Get him out of here.

903
02:45:22 --> 02:45:32
- I'll see you later.
- Why are you going back?

904
02:45:33 --> 02:45:43
[GUNSHOTS]

905
02:45:44 --> 02:45:54
[CROWD SCREAMING]

906
02:45:55 --> 02:46:05
Get out of here.

907
02:46:06 --> 02:46:16
Tell me what you know about the Joker.

908
02:46:17 --> 02:46:27
[CHUCKLING]

909
02:46:28 --> 02:46:38
[ENGINE STARTS]

910
02:46:39 --> 02:46:49
No.

911
02:46:50 --> 02:47:00
I'm sorry, Barbara.

912
02:47:01 --> 02:47:11
Jimmy, go play with your sister.
Go ahead, honey.

913
02:47:12 --> 02:47:22
STEPHENS: If there's anything
we can do, anything you need...

914
02:47:23 --> 02:47:33
...we're here for you.

915
02:47:34 --> 02:47:44
[BARBARA SOBBING]

916
02:47:45 --> 02:47:55
Shh.

917
02:47:56 --> 02:48:06
BARBARA:
Are you out there?

918
02:48:07 --> 02:48:17
Are you? You brought this
craziness on us. You did!

919
02:48:18 --> 02:48:28
You brought this on us!

920
02:48:29 --> 02:48:39
Switch it off, he ain't coming.
He doesn't wanna talk to us.

921
02:48:40 --> 02:48:50
God help whoever
he does wanna talk to.

922
02:48:51 --> 02:49:01
[DANCE MUSIC PLAYING]

923
02:49:02 --> 02:49:12
Can't we go someplace quieter?
We can't hear each other talk.

924
02:49:13 --> 02:49:23
What makes you think
I wanna hear you talk?

925
02:49:24 --> 02:49:34
What?

926
02:49:35 --> 02:49:45
[GRUNTING]

927
02:49:46 --> 02:49:56
[CROWD SCREAMING]

928
02:49:57 --> 02:50:07
- Yeah?
MAN: Second.

929
02:50:08 --> 02:50:18
Okay.

930
02:50:19 --> 02:50:29
- Harvey, where are you?
DENT: <i>Where are you?</i>

931
02:50:30 --> 02:50:40
I'm where you should be,
at Major Crimes.

932
02:50:41 --> 02:50:51
I'm trying to deal with all of this mess.

933
02:50:52 --> 02:51:02
- Can I get the fingerprint analysis?
<i>- Rachel, listen. You're not safe there.</i>

934
02:51:03 --> 02:51:13
- This is Gordon's unit.
<i>- Gordon 's gone.</i>

935
02:51:14 --> 02:51:24
RACHEL: He vouched for these men.
<i>- And he's gone.</i>

936
02:51:25 --> 02:51:35
<i>The Joker's named you next.</i>

937
02:51:36 --> 02:51:46
<i>God, is there someone, is there anyone</i>
<i>in this town we can trust?</i>

938
02:51:47 --> 02:51:57
Bruce.

939
02:51:58 --> 02:52:08
We can trust Bruce Wayne.

940
02:52:09 --> 02:52:19
<i>No. Rachel, I know</i>
<i>you're his friend, but...</i>

941
02:52:20 --> 02:52:30
Harvey, trust me.

942
02:52:31 --> 02:52:41
Bruce's penthouse is now
the safest place in the city.

943
02:52:42 --> 02:52:52
<i>Then you go straight there.</i>

944
02:52:53 --> 02:53:03
<i>Don 't tell anybody</i>
<i>and I'll find you there.</i>

945
02:53:04 --> 02:53:14
I love you.

946
02:53:15 --> 02:53:25
I want the Joker.

947
02:53:26 --> 02:53:36
From one professional to another...

948
02:53:37 --> 02:53:47
...you're trying to scare somebody,
pick a better spot.

949
02:53:48 --> 02:53:58
From this height,
the fall wouldn't kill me.

950
02:53:59 --> 02:54:09
- I'm counting on it.
- Huh!

951
02:54:10 --> 02:54:20
[SCREAMS]

952
02:54:21 --> 02:54:31
[BONE CRACKS]
[MARONI YELLS]

953
02:54:32 --> 02:54:42
[MARONI WHEEZING]

954
02:54:43 --> 02:54:53
- Where is he?
- I don't know where he is. He found us.

955
02:54:54 --> 02:55:04
He must have friends.

956
02:55:05 --> 02:55:15
Friends? Have you met this guy?

957
02:55:16 --> 02:55:26
Someone knows where he is.

958
02:55:27 --> 02:55:37
Nobody's gonna tell you nothing.

959
02:55:38 --> 02:55:48
They're wise to your act.

960
02:55:49 --> 02:55:59
You got rules.
The Joker, he's got no rules.

961
02:56:00 --> 02:56:10
Nobody's gonna cross him for you.
If you want this guy, you got one way.

962
02:56:11 --> 02:56:21
But you already know what that is.

963
02:56:22 --> 02:56:32
Just take off that mask,
let him come find you.

964
02:56:33 --> 02:56:43
[GROWLS]

965
02:56:44 --> 02:56:54
Or you can let a couple more people
get killed while you make up your mind.

966
02:56:55 --> 02:57:05
You wanna play games?

967
02:57:06 --> 02:57:16
[GUNSHOT]

968
02:57:17 --> 02:57:27
How's that feel?

969
02:57:28 --> 02:57:38
- You wouldn't.
- I wouldn't!

970
02:57:39 --> 02:57:49
- You don't think I will?
- Mm-mm.

971
02:57:50 --> 02:58:00
- You don't think I will?
- Mm-mm.

972
02:58:01 --> 02:58:11
No. No, I wouldn't.

973
02:58:12 --> 02:58:22
That's why I'm not
gonna leave it up to me.

974
02:58:23 --> 02:58:33
Heads, you get to keep your head.

975
02:58:34 --> 02:58:44
Tails...

976
02:58:45 --> 02:58:55
...not so lucky.

977
02:58:56 --> 02:59:06
So you wanna tell me about the Joker?

978
02:59:07 --> 02:59:17
[THUG CHUCKLES]

979
02:59:18 --> 02:59:28
- Let's go again.
- I don't know anything! God, don't!

980
02:59:29 --> 02:59:39
You're not playing the odds, friend.

981
02:59:40 --> 02:59:50
Let's do it again.

982
02:59:51 --> 03:00:01
You'd leave a man's life to chance?

983
03:00:02 --> 03:00:12
- Not exactly.
- His name's Schiff, Thomas.

984
03:00:13 --> 03:00:23
He's a paranoid schizophrenic,
former patient at Arkham.

985
03:00:24 --> 03:00:34
The kind of mind the Joker attracts.
What do you expect to learn from him?

986
03:00:35 --> 03:00:45
The Joker killed Gordon.
He's gonna kill Rachel.

987
03:00:46 --> 03:00:56
You're the symbol of hope
I could never be.

988
03:00:57 --> 03:01:07
Your stand against organized crime...

989
03:01:08 --> 03:01:18
...is the first legitimate ray of light
in Gotham in decades.

990
03:01:19 --> 03:01:29
If anyone saw this,
everything would be undone.

991
03:01:30 --> 03:01:40
The criminals you arrested
would be released...

992
03:01:41 --> 03:01:51
...and Jim Gordon
will have died for nothing.

993
03:01:52 --> 03:02:02
You're gonna hold
a press conference tomorrow.

994
03:02:03 --> 03:02:13
- Why?
- No one else will die because of me.

995
03:02:14 --> 03:02:24
Gotham's in your hands now.

996
03:02:25 --> 03:02:35
You can't.

997
03:02:36 --> 03:02:46
You can't give in.

998
03:02:47 --> 03:02:57
You can't give in!

999
03:02:58 --> 03:03:08
Harvey called.

1000
03:03:09 --> 03:03:19
He said Batman's gonna turn himself in.

1001
03:03:20 --> 03:03:30
I have no choice.

1002
03:03:31 --> 03:03:41
You honestly think that's gonna
keep the Joker from killing people?

1003
03:03:42 --> 03:03:52
Maybe not. But I have enough blood
on my hands.

1004
03:03:53 --> 03:04:03
And I've seen now what I would
have to become to stop men like him.

1005
03:04:04 --> 03:04:14
You once told me that
if the day came when I was finished...

1006
03:04:15 --> 03:04:25
...that we'd be together.

1007
03:04:26 --> 03:04:36
Bruce, don't make me
your one hope for a normal life.

1008
03:04:37 --> 03:04:47
Did you mean it?

1009
03:04:48 --> 03:04:58
Yes.

1010
03:04:59 --> 03:05:09
Bruce.

1011
03:05:10 --> 03:05:20
If you turn yourself in,
they're not gonna let us be together.

1012
03:05:21 --> 03:05:31
ALFRED: Logs as well?
BRUCE: Everything.

1013
03:05:32 --> 03:05:42
Anything that could lead back
to Lucius or Rachel.

1014
03:05:43 --> 03:05:53
People are dying, Alfred.
What would you have me do?

1015
03:05:54 --> 03:06:04
Endure, Master Wayne. Take it.

1016
03:06:05 --> 03:06:15
They'll hate you for it,
but that's the point of Batman.

1017
03:06:16 --> 03:06:26
He can be the outcast. He can make
the choice that no one else can make.

1018
03:06:27 --> 03:06:37
The right choice.

1019
03:06:38 --> 03:06:48
No, today I found out
what Batman can't do.

1020
03:06:49 --> 03:06:59
He can't endure this.

1021
03:07:00 --> 03:07:10
Today you get to say "I told you so."

1022
03:07:11 --> 03:07:21
Today, I don't want to.

1023
03:07:22 --> 03:07:32
But I did bloody tell you.

1024
03:07:33 --> 03:07:43
[BRUCE CHUCKLES]

1025
03:07:44 --> 03:07:54
ALFRED: I suppose they're gonna
lock me up as well...

1026
03:07:55 --> 03:08:05
...as your accomplice.

1027
03:08:06 --> 03:08:16
BRUCE: Accomplice? I'm gonna tell them
the whole thing was your idea.

1028
03:08:17 --> 03:08:27
Ladies and gentlemen, I've called
this press conference for two reasons.

1029
03:08:28 --> 03:08:38
Firstly, to assure the citizens
of Gotham...

1030
03:08:39 --> 03:08:49
...that everything that can be done
over the Joker killings is being done.

1031
03:08:50 --> 03:09:00
[CHATTERING]

1032
03:09:01 --> 03:09:11
Secondly, because the Batman
has offered to turn himself in.

1033
03:09:12 --> 03:09:22
<i>But let's consider the situation.</i>

1034
03:09:23 --> 03:09:33
Should we give in
to this terrorist's demands?

1035
03:09:34 --> 03:09:44
Do we really think he's gonna...?

1036
03:09:45 --> 03:09:55
You'd rather protect an outlaw vigilante
than the lives of citizens?

1037
03:09:56 --> 03:10:06
The Batman is an outlaw.

1038
03:10:07 --> 03:10:17
That's not why we demand
he turn himself in...

1039
03:10:18 --> 03:10:28
...we're doing it because we're scared.

1040
03:10:29 --> 03:10:39
We've been happy to let Batman
clean up our streets till now.

1041
03:10:40 --> 03:10:50
MAN 1: Things are worse than ever!
MAN 2: Amen.

1042
03:10:51 --> 03:11:01
Yes, they are.

1043
03:11:02 --> 03:11:12
But the night is darkest
just before the dawn.

1044
03:11:13 --> 03:11:23
And I promise you...

1045
03:11:24 --> 03:11:34
...the dawn is coming.

1046
03:11:35 --> 03:11:45
One day, the Batman will have to answer
for the laws he's broken. But to us...

1047
03:11:46 --> 03:11:56
...not to this madman.

1048
03:11:57 --> 03:12:07
- No more dead cops!
OFFICERS: Yeah!

1049
03:12:08 --> 03:12:18
He should turn himself in!

1050
03:12:19 --> 03:12:29
MAN 3: Give us the Batman! Come on!
MAN 4: Where is he?

1051
03:12:30 --> 03:12:40
So be it. Take the Batman into custody.

1052
03:12:41 --> 03:12:51
WOMAN: What?
MAN 5: Is he here?

1053
03:12:52 --> 03:13:02
I am the Batman.

1054
03:13:03 --> 03:13:13
MAN 6: What?
MAN 7: Come on.

1055
03:13:14 --> 03:13:24
RACHEL:
Alfred.

1056
03:13:25 --> 03:13:35
Why is he letting Harvey do this?

1057
03:13:36 --> 03:13:46
- He went down to the press conference.
- I know. He just stood by.

1058
03:13:47 --> 03:13:57
Perhaps both Bruce and Mr. Dent...

1059
03:13:58 --> 03:14:08
...believe that Batman stands for
something more important...

1060
03:14:09 --> 03:14:19
...than the whims of a terrorist,
Miss Dawes...

1061
03:14:20 --> 03:14:30
...even if everyone hates him for it.

1062
03:14:31 --> 03:14:41
That's the sacrifice he's making.

1063
03:14:42 --> 03:14:52
He's not being a hero.
He's being something more.

1064
03:14:53 --> 03:15:03
Yeah, you're absolutely right.

1065
03:15:04 --> 03:15:14
Letting Harvey take the fall for this
is not heroic at all.

1066
03:15:15 --> 03:15:25
You know him better than anyone.

1067
03:15:26 --> 03:15:36
I do.

1068
03:15:37 --> 03:15:47
Will you give this to him for me?
When the time is right?

1069
03:15:48 --> 03:15:58
How will I know?

1070
03:15:59 --> 03:16:09
It's not sealed.

1071
03:16:10 --> 03:16:20
Goodbye, Alfred.

1072
03:16:21 --> 03:16:31
Bye, Rachel.

1073
03:16:32 --> 03:16:42
[CELL DOOR OPENS]

1074
03:16:43 --> 03:16:53
I didn't have time to talk this through.

1075
03:16:54 --> 03:17:04
What are you doing?

1076
03:17:05 --> 03:17:15
They're transferring me
to Central Holding.

1077
03:17:16 --> 03:17:26
This is the Joker's chance, and when he
attacks, the Batman will take him down.

1078
03:17:27 --> 03:17:37
Listen. This is too dangerous.

1079
03:17:38 --> 03:17:48
We get this guy to County, he's their
problem. The streets will be cleared...

1080
03:17:49 --> 03:17:59
...so let's go.
The convoys stop for no reason.

1081
03:18:00 --> 03:18:10
I hope you got some moves, pal.

1082
03:18:11 --> 03:18:21
He's using you as bait. He doesn't
know if he can get the Joker.

1083
03:18:22 --> 03:18:32
He's failed so far.

1084
03:18:33 --> 03:18:43
How do you know
what he's thinking?

1085
03:18:44 --> 03:18:54
I just do. Anyway,
this isn't just about you.

1086
03:18:55 --> 03:19:05
What about the people
depending on you...

1087
03:19:06 --> 03:19:16
